I love this game and always have since I first played the original board game.  The problems with this version are really only small issues, but deserves the loss of 1 star.    As others have mentioned, it really needs [at least] a pass and play option, and and option to turn down certain sound effects, (ie the sound of the tile play is fine, but the constant beeping and whistling are not needed).  Oh, and also, why have a help button in the credits that doesn't actually do anything?????

Firstly lets not take anything away from Rummikub itself as it is still one of the most entertaining board games around but this application is beyond pathetic.  1) There's no multi-player (online or local). What is the point in having Rummikub when you can't play the game against an actual person.  2) The CPU can move groups of tiles and can do the most amazing things in 60 seconds but you can't. If you want to break up a "run" you have to break it up one by one.  3) There's no actual score. Yes you can see at the end of a round how much you scored for that particular round but there's no actual score in the game itself. i.e. all you can actually play is one round of Rummikub  4) The AI is ridiculously stupid. At least 70% of the time they leave the joker at the end of an open set which allows the user to always have a free joker. The AI will also have ALL of the tiles racked but will be "unable" to play.  5) There are silly bugs like not always splitting sets properly when a tile is placed on the board. However, whenever the AI does this (yes, the AI is also affected by the bugs) the game crashes.  Speak about value for money, you're better off doing a crossword.

I love this game but when I purchased a new phone I was unable to download it  To my new one. I kept getting a message that it was already installed, and when I tried to reinstall it would not let me, so I am without the game on my new  phone - very disappointing.
